<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2018-06-19</DATELINE><TITLE>Holy Immune Tolerance, Batman!</TITLE><BODY>Bats are reservoir hosts of numerous viruses that cause severe pathology in humans. How bats cope with such pathogens remains elusive. In a recent issue of Cell, Pavlovich et al. (2018) describe several key adaptations in innate immune-related genes that suggest that the Egyptian rousette fruit bat relies on immune tolerance mechanisms to manage viral infections.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>